26/04/2005
WASHINGTON, United States -- The ambassadors of the Adriatic Charter signatories -- Albania, Croatia and Macedonia -- reiterated on Monday (25 April) that their countries expect a NATO invitation during the Alliance's next summit in 2006, followed by membership in 2008. The ambassadors to the United States made the joint statement during a roundtable dedicated to the upcoming second anniversary of the sealing of the Charter. 
In other news, Macedonian Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva travels Tuesday to Brussels for talks with the North Atlantic Council. The focus will be on issues related to Macedonia's bid for Euro-Atlantic integration, as well as realisation of the NATO Membership Action Plan. (Makfax - 26/04/05)
